<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The lfs_cache struct member uint8_t *buffer is a non-const pointer but is used via const lfs_cache_t *pcache (e.g. in lfs_bd_read). Rule 8.13 expects pointers to point to const-qualified data when they are used read-only. Here pcache is intended read-only, yet its buffer points to non-const uint8_t, allowing modification of the pointed data; this violates the guideline that pointers should point to const-qualified type whenever possible.
</scenario>

